<div class="row">
  <div class="col-lg-6">
    <h1>Export</h1>
    <h2>Exporting to MapStory</h2>
    <p>MapStory accepts temporally sequenced sets of raster images. 
      To add the images you warp here, simply download them to your 
      desktop and upload them as a single zipped file to MapStory. 
      Thereâ€™s more 
      directions <a href="http://mapstory.org/mapstory/manual/#prep-raster" target="_blank">here</a>.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="col-lg-6">
    <h2>Downloads</h2>

    <h3>GeoTiff</h3>
    <p>Rectified output, best format for MapStory<br>
      <%= link_to  "<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-download'></span> GeoTiff", export_map_url(:id => @map, :format => :tif), :class => "btn btn-default" %>
    </p>

    <h3>PNG</h3>
    <p>
      Rectified output<br>
      <%= link_to  "<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-download'></span> PNG", export_map_url(:id => @map, :format => :png), :class => "btn btn-default" %>
      <%= link_to "<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-download'></span> .aux.xml", export_map_url(:id => @map, :format => :aux_xml), :class => "btn btn-default" %>
    </p>

    <h3>KML</h3>
    <p>
    <%= link_to("<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-download'></span> KML",  map_url(:id => @map, :format => :kml), :class => "btn btn-default") %>
    <%= link_to("<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-new-window'></span> View in Google Maps", "http://maps.google.com?q="+map_url(:id => @map, :format => :kml), :class => "btn btn-default", :target => "_blank") %>
    </p>

    <h3>Gaia GPS</h3>
    <p>Export directly to <a href="https://www.gaiagps.com/gallery/">Gaia GPS</a> applications<br>
      <%=link_to "<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-export'></span> Gaia GPS", @gaia_url, :class => "btn btn-default" %>
      <%=link_to "<span class='glyphicon glyphicon-export'></span> Offline Topo Maps", @otm_url, :class => "btn btn-default" %>
    </p>

    <h3>WMS &amp; Tiles</h3>
    <p>You can reference this map from other applications. Use the following URL formats:</p>

    <% josm_url = url_for(wms_map_url(:id => @map)) + "?request=GetMap&version=1.1.1&styles=&format=image/png&srs=epsg:4326&exceptions=application/vnd.ogc.session.inimage&" %>
    <% tile_url = url_for(:controller => "maps", :action => "tile", :x => "x", :y => "y", :z => "z", :only_path => false) %>

    <ul>
      <li><%= link_to "WMS base URL", wms_map_url(:id=>@map) %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "WMS for JOSM OpenStreetMap Editor", josm_url %></li>
      <li><%= link_to "Tile Path", tile_url %> (Google/OSM scheme)</li>
    </ul>

  </div>
</div>